3229d9df-47d3-4c27-84e9-926cc396fdb2.1505cf22-a3ba-4be3-9b43-bdfabe1e5aa4.description=
Computes a mathematical operation.

Input Parameters\:
value1 - the first value
value2 - the second value
operator - operation to perform (+,-,*,/,%);

Responses\:
success - the expression was evaluated.
failure - the expression could not be evaluated.

Returns\: the value of the expression.

3229d9df-47d3-4c27-84e9-926cc396fdb2.4b550436-942f-4f8b-a6e9-fe3dcac96551.prompt=enter a value for host 3229d9df-47d3-4c27-84e9-926cc396fdb2.86cb509a-4db4-4962-a25b-5fbeb9ce21a4.description=
Adds a value into the global context (available to all parent and child flows)

Input Parameters\:
keyName - the name of the context variable to use
myValue - the value to assign the context variable

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Scriptlet Example\:
[$scriptletContext putGlobal\: $keyName, $myValue];
3229d9df-47d3-4c27-84e9-926cc396fdb2.a9b86099-a928-4ab0-93c4-81a53a51c411.prompt=Input username\: 3229d9df-47d3-4c27-84e9-926cc396fdb2.description=
Gets several common windows performance counters.
WMI query does not work in Windows 2000, Windows NT 4.0, and Windows Me/98/95.

Inputs\:
host - host to query.
username - username to authenticate with.
password - password for host.

Result\:
a comma separated list of performance counter values.

Extra Results\:
header - a header that states what each counter value is.
data - result of the operation execution.

Responses\:
success - operation completed.
failure - something went wrong.
